articles.description: Xavier senior Sean O'Mara can usually find a couple of extra tickets for his family and friends from teammates, some of which are from far away as Georgia, New Jersey and even Turkey.
articles.headline: Weekend lookahead: Xavier, Villanova battle for Big East supremacy

images.caption: Xavier can avenge its Jan. 10 loss to Villanova when the Wildcats visit on Saturday.
images.name: Tyrique Jones [576x324]

articles.description: After being asked to not single out Arizona State players using his megaphone, an Arizona cheerleader continued to heckle and was ejected.

articles.description: Malachi Flynn scored a career high 30 points and Washington State rallied late to defeat Colorado 73-69 on Thursday night to end a seven-game losing streak.
articles.headline: Washington St defeats Colorado 73-69 behind Flynn's 30

articles.description: No. 16 Rhode Island has a school-record 16-game winning streak, but there is cause for concern with the left knee injury suffered by fifth-year senior guard E.C. Matthews on Tuesday in a victory over Richmond.
articles.headline: Rhode Island-St. Bonaventure Preview

articles.description: Gibson Johnson and Sheriff Drammeh scored 13 apiece and Michael Thomas hit four free throws in the final 41 seconds to help Hawaii cool off UC Irvine 62-61 on Thursday night, ending the Anteaters' five-game win streak.
articles.headline: Hawaii outlasts UC Irvine 62-61

videos.description: Sagaba Konate gets the block but Khadeem Lattin stays with the play and gets the second-chance bucket.
videos.headline: Lattin gets bucket after big WVU block

videos.description: Jevon Carter locks down Trae Young and forces a turnover.
videos.headline: WVU's Carter strips Trae Young

videos.description: Trae Young pulls up from way behind the 3-point line but misses to set up an easy transition layup for Maciej Bender.
videos.headline: Young's long miss leads to Bender layup

videos.description: Jevon Carter has the advantage early on in his showdown with Trae Young with a steal and a block on consecutive possessions.
videos.headline: Carter locks up Young on back-to-back possessions

videos.description: Jamuni McNeace rises up off an inbounds pass from Trae Young for the explosive jam.
videos.headline: Oklahoma's McNeace throws down alley-oop slam

videos.description: Jevon Carter makes a move to get by Trae Young and knocks down the baseline jumper.
videos.headline: Carter blows by Young and knocks down the jumper

videos.description: Jevon Carter misses a layup but grabs the rebound and knocks down a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Carter sticks with play and knocks down 3-pointer

videos.description: James Bolden gets Trae Young in the air and hits the 3-pointer for West Virginia.
videos.headline: WVU's Bolden fakes Young and knocks down 3-pointer

videos.description: Trae Young pulls up with no hesitation from way behind the 3-point line and knocks it down.
videos.headline: Young buries 3-pointer from Steph Curry range

videos.description: Trae Young finds Khadeem Lattin with a great pass that leads to a bucket and the foul.
videos.headline: Young drops a dime to Lattin

videos.description: Trae Young knocks down a deep 3-pointer to keep Oklahoma in the game late.
videos.headline: Young from way downtown

videos.description: Teddy Allen finishes with a slam as West Virginia beats Oklahoma 89-76.
videos.headline: Allen finishes Oklahoma with breakaway slam
